{"word":"ξυρήκης","slug":"ξυρήκης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ξυρήκης</b></el> <el>(ξῠρ-ήκης, ες) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἀκη</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>keen as a rasor</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>close-shaven</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>κουρᾷ ξυρήκει</el> with <i>close</i> tonsure, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}